00:21:53.247 --> 00:21:56.961
burned at the stake, killed by being burned alive.

00:21:58.021 --> 00:21:59.871
But there was a way out.

00:22:00.911 --> 00:22:07.541
If she signed a document declaring that her visions of God were a lie, and that she promised to

00:22:07.541 --> 00:22:13.031
stop wearing men’s clothes, she would be saved, she would only have to face life imprisonment.

00:22:14.321 --> 00:22:18.041
She signed the document, and was saved from the flames.

00:22:19.441 --> 00:22:24.481
But just four days later she went back on this, she rejected her rejection.

00:22:25.771 --> 00:22:30.361
She yet again put on the uniform of a male soldier, saying that St

00:22:30.361 --> 00:22:34.221
Catherine and St Margaret had told her off for giving in so easily.

00:22:35.761 --> 00:22:38.331
By now, her fate was sealed.

00:22:39.381 --> 00:22:46.701
On May the 29th of 1431 she was led to the town square at Rouen, placed on

00:22:46.731 --> 00:22:52.811
